rial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utahliatreekin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tahlia Treekin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Thug of Nature</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>21</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>1:13:23 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I am a taxi driver</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">That is it I have had it. I think if I had to start my druid again I wouldn't buy grp tp spells. <br>
<br>
Wednesday night a cleric ask me to take him to Iceclad. I told him that I was logging and I didn't have the time. He continues that he wants me to take him to Iceclad, lead him over to Thurg, help him find his new spell, and then bring him home. At this point I stopped camping and told him that I am a taxi driver. I pick you up and drop you off. Taxi drivers do not pick you up, take you to the mall, guide you around, help you buy something from a mall store and then take you home. Then I sat down and camped out.<br>
<br>
After camping out I brought on my other toon who was at the same ring and asked this cleric for a cure. He told me he was in /role for a reason and that reason was to not be bothered. I literally laughed out loud because my druid now stays in /role so that I have a sparse chance of enjoying her.<br>
<br>
Thursday night I go to pick up a guildie at the LS ring when Murda asks me for a tp to WC. I explained that I was picking up someone to help with CR and didn't have time but that WC was only two zones over and since he was invis when he asked he should be safe going thru Nek. I gave him a sow and started casting to take my guildie out when Murda said he had been at LS for two hours and he cancelled the sow because he wants a tp to WC and he will wait as long as it takes.<br>
<br>
I like helping out ppl when I can and after that first week at 29 I have never charged someone for a tp.  Although I do except money it if given to me. +) Have I been too nice that these two examples grate against my skin?</font><P>Tahlia Treekin <BR>
Level 50 Druid <BR>
Smartass of Tunare <P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urexron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexron</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The Pie Guy </FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>155</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>2:26:57 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: I am a taxi driver</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">*SMILE*<br>
Well .. thanks to Verant, Druids are no longers the masters of movement.  If you haven't noticed, only wizzies are getting translocates.  And, apparently, ONLY wizzies are getting the Luclin ports.  So ... dispair no more.<br>
<br>
I have never /anon or /roll on my druid for 51 levels of druid and 41 levels of cleric.  Never will either.<br>
<br>
I take who I can when I can, guild, friend, or stranger.  If I cant, i dont.  I never, ever ignore anyone.  When I get those freakin random tells, I very nicely let them know I cant.  I always give a polite reason and ALWAYS apologize.  I have only had 2 or 3 people ever give me flak about it.  Those people get ignored.<br>
<br>
I think it's all a matter of who you are and how you handle it.  Some people are too darned nice and just cant say no.  I'm not that person.  Others get sucked into the guild trips or sob stories.  OH I am not that person =)  I am steadfast in saying no, and don't waver.  I will always help my guildies, but I've even told some of them no.  They understand and respect that I play this game for my enjoyment and exp and loot, not just to move people around.<br>
<br>
For people who demand ports, like that guy who cancelled his sow, just be really blunt with him.  "I'm sorry you can't get a port right now.  I've got to take care of xxx, yyy, and zzz.  Good luck to you."  And just drop it.  If he tells you again, and doesnt say "NP" or "I understand, thx anyway" .. but instead gives you "Come on, it'll only take 5 min"  or my favorite, "dude, come on, mana's free".  Just have a pair of "balls" and say:<br>
"I declined you nicely twice, yet you rudely persist.  I'm sorry, but I've got to add you to my ignore list.  I really thought you'd respect me more.  Bye"<br>
and just do it.  If it's a guildie, then they dont respect teammates.  If it's a friend, they're not much of a friend.  And If it's some stranger, who cares anyway.  They cant respect you, dont respect them.<br>
